  {"a":"ezreal_bot","b":"vayne","win":["Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Vayne","Ezreal"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once you have Q-W-Q online you outrange Vayne massively: her Tumble (Q) auto-reset only works inside 550 range, so poke her every time she walks up to last-hit and she bleeds without ever touching you. Land Mystic Shot (Q) on minions she's about to CS to zone her off the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Vayne's power comes online here: Final Hour (R) gives her bonus AD, faster Tumble stealth, and heavy invisibility on Q, letting her all-in you. Hold Arcane Shift (E) purely to break her Condemn (E) stun-to-wall and to reposition out of her three-Silver-Bolt burst; do not waste it as aggression."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Vayne's first-item spike into Blade of the Ruined King plus stealth makes short trades dangerous, so respect her all-in windows when her jungler is bot. Keep farming safely with Q and only commit when her R or E is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your poke identity wins: Vayne must stat-check through her true-damage bolts at close range while you kite from max distance, chunking her with Q every 2-4 seconds. In teamfights spot her from the backline and E away the instant she Condemns."}],"wants":{"you":["Long trades where you Q from max range and never let her stack 3 Silver Bolts","E saved for her Condemn (E) and reposition, not for damage","Poke her low before level 6 so Final Hour is a defensive tool not an all-in"],"foe":["A gap-close and stealth-Tumble reset to stack true-damage bolts on you","Level 6 Final Hour plus jungle CC to all-in through your E","Side-terrain to Condemn (E) stun you against a wall"]},"early":"You dominate levels 1-2: Vayne has no range and no early poke, so hit her with Mystic Shot every time she steps up to CS and deny her free farm while you last-hit safely behind minions.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay yours because your Q outranges her entire kit and her Tumble reset only fires point-blank; keep spacing, poke on her walk-ups, and refuse the close-range brawl she wants. She has no way to force you before Final Hour comes online.","late":"After Final Hour and Blade of the Ruined King her level-6 all-in flips the lane briefly, but with two items your max-range Q poke and E disengage let you out-space her again into every teamfight.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Vayne is short-ranged with no poke while your auto-Q already threatens her walk-ups.","Level 2 favours you: your second point in Q lets you harass her off the wave before she has any trading tool.","Level 3 favours you: full Q-W-E means you outrange and out-poke her non-existent early damage.","Levels 4-5 favour you: you keep chunking her from range while her Tumble reset can't reach you.","Level 6 is still yours: your poke lead means her fresh Final Hour is forced to play defensive.","First item favours Vayne: her Blade of the Ruined King plus stealth spike gives her a real all-in window on you.","Two-plus items favour you: max-range Q kiting and E disengage beat her close-range stat-check in extended fights."]},
  {"a":"ezreal_bot","b":"veigar","win":["Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Veigar","Ezreal"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Veigar bot is immobile and reliant on landing Baleful Strike (Q) to farm and stack AP, so weave Mystic Shot (Q) into him whenever he steps up to CS. Your range and E mobility mean his slow, telegraphed Dark Matter (W) almost never lands on you, and you can shove-and-poke him flat."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Event Horizon (E) plus Primordial Burst (R) is his kill combo: if his cage clips you, R can delete you outright at low health. Save Arcane Shift (E) to blink out of the stun ring rather than into it, and never dash toward him when his R is up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is Veigar's spike: with his first AP item and R rank-up his Primordial Burst executes you if you're caught by the cage, so play around the wave and respect his all-in when he has flash or jungle CC to guarantee the E."},{"when":"Late","text":"With two items your safe max-range Q poke and constant E repositioning let you whittle him without entering cage range; in fights hang at the very back so his Event Horizon can't wall you and force him to blow R on a frontliner instead of you."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke him off Baleful Strike stacks so his AP scaling stays low","E held to break Event Horizon (E), never to dash inward","Long-range Q trades that punish his zero mobility"],"foe":["Landing Event Horizon (E) to lock you for the Primordial Burst (R) execute","Flash or jungle CC to guarantee the cage stun","You dashing into cage range with E on cooldown"]},"early":"You out-tempo Veigar levels 1-2: he has no waveclear or poke yet and must risk walk-ups for Baleful Strike, so tag him with Mystic Shot each time and last-hit comfortably from range.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay in your favour because his damage is single-target and slow; dodge Dark Matter on reaction, keep Q poking, and shove so he's stuck farming under tower where he can't threaten you. His only kill tool, the cage combo, isn't reliable yet.","late":"His first-item Primordial Burst spike is the danger window: one Event Horizon into R can execute you, so respect it, but with two items and disciplined E usage your poke and disengage reassert control every fight.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Veigar has no early poke and must expose himself to farm while your Q already harasses.","Level 2 favours you: added Q rank lets you punish his Baleful Strike walk-ups freely.","Level 3 favours you: full kit outranges him and his Dark Matter is too slow to punish your spacing.","Levels 4-5 favour you: continued Q poke keeps his AP stacks and health low with no reliable answer.","Level 6 is still yours: without a guaranteed cage his fresh R can't catch you through your E and range.","First item favours Veigar: his AP spike lets Primordial Burst execute you if Event Horizon lands.","Two-plus items favour you: max-range poke and backline spacing dodge his cage and win the long game."]},
  {"a":"ezreal_bot","b":"xayah","win":["Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Ezreal"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Xayah out-trades you early because her Double Daggers (Q) and stacked feathers give her burst poke and lane sustain, while your Mystic Shot is your only reliable damage. She drops feathers on the wave and callbacks them with Bladecaller (E) to root you, so stand away from clustered feathers and never trade into a full feather pile."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Deadly Plumage (W) plus Featherstorm (R) is a huge spike: W gives her attack speed and movement, and R makes her untargetable while raining feathers she'll recall to root. Hold Arcane Shift (E) to dodge the Bladecaller root that follows her R, since that root is what sets up her all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her first-item spike with W active lets her win most extended trades and all-ins, especially with a support root or engage. Play safe, farm with Q, and don't contest her when her feathers are stacked and W is up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you finally pull ahead: your max-range Q poke and E mobility let you kite her outside feather-callback range, and in fights you dodge her Bladecaller root with E while chunking her from distance. Never stand on her feather lines and she loses her only lockdown on you."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm from max range and refuse trades near clustered feathers","E saved specifically for her Bladecaller (E) root","Scale to two items where your poke and disengage out-space her"],"foe":["Stacked feathers plus Bladecaller (E) to root you into a trade","Level 6 W-plus-R attack-speed spike for the all-in","A support engage or root to guarantee her callback lands"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Xayah: her Double Daggers poke and feather sustain beat your single-target Q, so give ground, last-hit safely, and avoid standing where her feathers can be recalled.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay hers because Bladecaller can root you off any feather pile and her W trade pattern out-DPSes you up close; keep the wave moving, dodge feather lines, and hold E for the root instead of poke. Don't let her stack a lane-winning lead here.","late":"Her feather-and-W identity keeps her ahead through first item, but once you hit two items your range and E disengage flip it: kite outside callback range, dodge the root, and out-poke her into every teamfight.","whys":["Level 1 favours Xayah: her Q and feather poke out-trade your single-target Mystic Shot.","Level 2 favours Xayah: feather stacking gives her a burst and root threat you can't match yet.","Level 3 favours Xayah: full Bladecaller lets her root you off feather piles for winning trades.","Levels 4-5 favour Xayah: her W trade pattern and feather lockdown keep her ahead in lane.","Level 6 favours Xayah: W-plus-Featherstorm gives her an untargetable all-in with a follow-up root.","First item favours Xayah: her W-active spike wins extended trades and all-ins outright.","Two-plus items favour you: max-range poke and E disengage finally out-space her callback root."]},
  {"a":"ezreal_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Zeri","Ezreal"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zeri's early is weak: her auto-Q does chip damage but her burst W (Ultrashock Laser) is a skillshot on a long cooldown, and she has to walk into range to farm. Poke her with Mystic Shot (Q) on every CS attempt and shove so she farms under tower, where her low early damage can't punish you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Lightspeed Strike (R) turns her into a hyper-mobile scaling threat, converting excess energy into attack speed and letting her dash-wall with E over terrain. Hold Arcane Shift (E) to match her repositioning and dodge her charged W; don't over-extend once her R is up because she can chase far."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is Zeri's spike: her first crit/attack-speed item plus R scaling makes her DPS and mobility snowball, so respect her chase and don't get caught in extended fights where her uptime beats yours. Keep poking from range and deny her the item lead."},{"when":"Late","text":"With two items your poke stays relevant because Zeri is squishy and her auto-Q is short-range; land Q from max distance and E away when she dashes in. In fights don't chase her mobility, just hold spacing and chunk her before her attack-speed R ramps up."}],"wants":{"you":["Punish her weak early with constant Q poke and tower-lock her farm","E held to mirror her E dash and dodge her charged W","Keep her off her first-item power spike by winning the early game"],"foe":["Reaching her R attack-speed scaling and item spike intact","Using E wall-dashes and R to chase you down in extended trades","Free early farm so she hits her damage items on time"]},"early":"You beat Zeri levels 1-2: her auto-Q is short-range chip and she lacks burst, so harass her with Mystic Shot on every walk-up and last-hit safely while she struggles to trade back.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay yours because your Q outranges her and her only burst, Ultrashock Laser, is a dodgeable long-cooldown skillshot; keep poking, shove her under tower, and starve her of the farm she needs to scale. This is your window to build a lead before she powers up.","late":"Her level-6 R and first attack-speed item flip the tempo as her DPS and mobility snowball, but with two items your max-range Q and E disengage keep chunking her squishy frame if you refuse to chase and hold spacing.","whys":["Level 1 favours you: Zeri's short-range auto-Q and no burst let your Mystic Shot harass freely.","Level 2 favours you: your Q poke punishes her weak early walk-ups before she has any trade tool.","Level 3 favours you: you outrange her and dodge her long-cooldown Ultrashock Laser easily.","Levels 4-5 favour you: continued poke and a tower-locked wave starve her scaling.","Level 6 is still yours: your lane lead means her fresh R can't yet out-damage your range and poke.","First item favours Zeri: her attack-speed and R scaling spike snowballs her DPS and mobility.","Two-plus items favour you: max-range Q and E disengage out-space her squishy short-range frame."]},
  {"a":"ezreal_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Ezreal","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs out-pokes you in this window: Bouncing Bomb (Q) has huge range and low cooldown for chip and waveclear, and Satchel Charge (W) plus Hexplosive Minefield (E) zone you off the wave. His bombs outrange your Mystic Shot, so last-hit from behind minions and don't walk into his minefield for CS."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You stabilize here: your level-6 identity is E-flash-Q burst and repositioning, and Ziggs' R (Mega Inferno Bomb) is a poke/zone tool, not a duel win-button. Use Arcane Shift (E) to dodge his Satchel knockback and close for a Q hit, then disengage before his bombs cycle back up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first item your Q poke and Sheen-style proc trades even; Ziggs is immobile aside from Satchel self-knockback, so punish his cooldowns. Land Q after he throws Q or E and you win the trade cleanly since he can't answer your range with his own on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you pull ahead: Ziggs is stationary and squishy, so weave Q from max range and E onto him whenever his Satchel is down. In fights he's a poke turret with no escape, so dodge his bombs behind minions and collapse when his W is on cooldown while you keep full mobility."}],"wants":{"you":["Scale past his early poke to where your Q and E mobility punish his immobility","E saved to dodge Satchel (W) knockback and close the gap","Trade after his Q or E is on cooldown so he can't answer"],"foe":["Long-range Bouncing Bomb (Q) poke and minefield zoning in the early-mid window","Satchel (W) plus Minefield (E) to keep you off the wave and chip you down","Free poke uptime while his bombs outrange your Mystic Shot"]},"early":"Level 1 is even-to-yours before his kit is online, but you must respect that his Q will soon outrange you; grab safe last-hits and avoid walking up into an early bomb.","mid":"Levels 2-5 belong to Ziggs: Bouncing Bomb poke, Satchel knockback, and the Hexplosive Minefield zone let him chip you and control the wave from outside your range, so farm from max distance behind minions and don't contest CS inside his minefield. Weather this window without giving up health or plates.","late":"From level 6 onward you take over: your E burst and repositioning punish his total lack of mobility, and with one then two items you land max-range Q on his cooldowns and collapse whenever his Satchel is down.","whys":["Level 1 is even-to-yours: Ziggs' poke kit isn't online yet so your Q and his auto trade evenly.","Level 2 favours Ziggs: Bouncing Bomb comes online and outranges your Mystic Shot for free chip.","Level 3 favours Ziggs: Satchel plus minefield let him zone you off the wave and poke safely.","Levels 4-5 favour Ziggs: his long-range bomb poke and zoning control the lane from outside your range.","Level 6 favours you: your E burst and repositioning punish his immobility while his R is only a poke tool.","First item favours you: your Q-Sheen trades beat him when his Q or E is on cooldown.","Two-plus items favour you: max-range poke and E mobility crush his stationary, escapeless frame."]}
